The course focuses on writing research papers in Estonian according to the principles of process-based writing. Students will learn how to:
- do preparatory work, including limiting the research topic, find academic information, apply reading methods;
- write the rough draft, including correct citing and referencing and automatic formatting of references;
- give other students effective feedback on texts and make changes in their own writing process based on feedback received;
- work in groups, in order to support writing process;
- format the text digitally.

The course is aimed primarily for third year BA students in order to support them in writing their research papers though practical classes and writing groups.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to improve students' writing and reading skills in order to support them in independent research.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course students: - follow the principles of good academic practices: - efficiently plan their writing process (including schedule, goals); - use relevant information retrieval methods and critically evaluate sources; - apply surface and deep reading methods for reading academic texts; - revise and format texts based on guidelines found in practical language management sources and elsewhere; - follow language and style guidelines on the text, paragraph, sentence and word level.
